title: Friday's Class 4A football recaps
text:
Friday’s Class 4A football recaps Register staff reports 11:25 p.m. CDT October 2, 2015 Johnston's T-Boy White pushes through a pack of Roosevelt defenders for a touchdown during Friday’s home game. White finished with a pair of scores and 71 rushing yards in the Dragons’ 49-0 victory. (Photo: Michael Zamora/The Register) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN 1 COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Dowling 59, S.C. East 21 
SIOUX CITY, Ia. – Dowling Catholic outscored Sioux City East 45-7 after being tied 14-all after the first quarter. 
Michael Zachary racked up 426 all-purpose yards with four touchdowns, while quarterback Kurt Walding only needed six completions to throw two touchdowns for the Maroons. 
Senior Dom Flemister had 117 receiving yards and a touchdown reception for Sioux City East.

Individual Leaders 
Rushing— Dowling Catholic: J. Zachary 6-92, M. Zachary 2-40-1; Sioux City East: Flemister 10-37, Skoglund 8-19-1. 
Passing— Dowling Catholic: Walding 6-11-118; Sioux City East: Koza 10-16-179. 
Receiving— Dowling Catholic: M. Zachary 3-108-2, Bliss 1-25-1; Sioux City East: D. Flemister 8-117-1. 
Lincoln 22, S.C. West 21 
Lincoln edged Sioux City West with a fourth-quarter touchdown by senior Richie Galvan. 
Sioux City West went into halftime with a 21-15 lead, but the Galvan touchdown gave the Railsplitters the one-point win. 
The teams went back and forth throughout, as Lincoln opened the scoring efforts with a 6-yard touchdown run by junior Brock Newton. Sioux City West responded with a touchdown by Samuel Blakey, but a field goal made it 9-7 Lincoln. 
Sioux City West would score one more time on an 80-yard touchdown throw from Noah McWell to Jalen Roseland in the second quarter.
